  "response": "To implement the `SecureStorage` class, I will first define the necessary interfaces in `src/providers/antigravity/oauth/types.ts` and then implement the encryption, keychain integration, and file storage logic in `src/providers/antigravity/oauth/secure-storage.ts`. I will use `AES-256-GCM` for encryption, `keytar` for OS keychain access, and a PBKDF2-derived key as a fallback. Atomic writes will be ensured by writing to a temporary file before renaming it to the target path.\n\n```json\n{\n  \"reasoning\": \"Implementing SecureStorage with AES-256-GCM and OS Keychain (keytar) integration. Includes a fallback mechanism using PBKDF2 derived from system identifiers for headless environments. Ensures atomic writes and secure file permissions (0o600).\",\n  \"changes\": [\n    {\n      \"file_path\": \"src/providers/antigravity/oauth/types.ts\",\n      \"content\": \"/**\\n * OAuth Credentials and Encryption Types\\n */\\n\\nexport interface OAuthCredentials {\\n  access_token: string;\\n  refresh_token?: string;\\n  expiry_date: number;\\n  token_type: string;\\n  email: string;\\n}\\n\\nexport interface EncryptedData {\\n  iv: string;           // Initialization vector (hex)\\n  authTag: string;      // Authentication tag (hex)\\n  data: string;         // Encrypted data (hex)\\n  algorithm: string;    // \\\"aes-256-gcm\\\"\\n  version: number;      // Format version for future compatibility\\n}\\n\\nexport interface SecureStorage {\\n  saveToken(email: string, credentials: OAuthCredentials): Promise<void>;\\n  loadToken(email: string): Promise<OAuthCredentials | null>;\\n  deleteToken(email: string): Promise<void>;\\n  listAccounts(): Promise<string[]>;\\n}\\n\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"file_path\": \"src/providers/antigravity/oauth/secure-storage.ts\",\n      \"content\": \"import * as crypto from 'crypto';\\nimport * as fs from 'fs-extra';\\nimport * as path from 'path';\\nimport * as os from 'os';\\nimport * as keytar from 'keytar';\\nimport { OAuthCredentials, EncryptedData, SecureStorage } from './types';\\n\\n/**\\n * Manages encryption keys using OS keychain with fallback to machine-specific derivation.\\n */\\nclass KeyStore {\\n  private readonly serviceName = 'cc-mirror-antigravity';\\n  private readonly accountName = 'encryption-key';\\n  private readonly fallbackSalt = 'cc-mirror-v1-salt-2026';\\n  private keyCache: Buffer | null = null;\\n\\n  async getKey(): Promise<Buffer> {\\n    if (this.keyCache) return this.keyCache;\\n\\n    try {\\n      const key = await this.getFromKeychain();\\n      if (key) {\\n        this.keyCache = key;\\n        return key;\\n      }\\n    } catch (error) {\\n      console.warn('[KeyStore] Keychain access failed, using fallback derivation');\\n    }\\n\\n    const key = await this.getFallbackKey();\\n    this.keyCache = key;\\n    return key;\\n  }\\n\\n  private async getFromKeychain(): Promise<Buffer | null> {\\n    try {\\n      let keyHex = await keytar.getPassword(this.serviceName, this.accountName);\\n      if (!keyHex) {\\n        keyHex = crypto.randomBytes(32).toString('hex');\\n        await keytar.setPassword(this.serviceName, this.accountName, keyHex);\\n      }\\n      return Buffer.from(keyHex, 'hex');\\n    } catch {\\n      return null;\\n    }\\n  }\\n\\n  private async getFallbackKey(): Promise<Buffer> {\\n    // Use stable identifiers for fallback key derivation\\n    const machineId = `${os.hostname()}-${os.arch()}-${os.platform()}`;\\n    return new Promise((resolve, reject) => {\\n      crypto.pbkdf2(machineId, this.fallbackSalt, 100000, 32, 'sha256', (err, key) => {\\n        if (err) reject(err);\\n        else resolve(key);\\n      });\\n    });\\n  }\\n}\\n\\n/**\\n * Secure storage for OAuth tokens using AES-256-GCM encryption.\\n */\\nexport class SecureTokenStorage implements SecureStorage {\\n  private readonly keyStore: KeyStore;\\n  private readonly tokenDir: string;\\n\\n  constructor(baseDir?: string) {\\n    this.keyStore = new KeyStore();\\n    this.tokenDir = baseDir || path.join(os.homedir(), '.cc-mirror', 'tokens');\\n    fs.ensureDirSync(this.tokenDir, { mode: 0o700 });\\n  }\\n\\n  async saveToken(email: string, credentials: OAuthCredentials): Promise<void> {\\n    const key = await this.keyStore.getKey();\\n    const encrypted = this.encrypt(credentials, key);\\n    const filePath = this.getTokenFilePath(email);\\n    const tempPath = `${filePath}.tmp`;\\n\\n    try {\\n      await fs.writeJSON(tempPath, encrypted, { mode: 0o600 });\\n      await fs.rename(tempPath, filePath);\\n    } catch (error) {\\n      if (await fs.pathExists(tempPath)) await fs.remove(tempPath);\\n      throw new Error(`Failed to save token for ${email}: ${error instanceof Error ? error.message : String(error)}`);\\n    }\\n  }\\n\\n  async loadToken(email: string): Promise<OAuthCredentials | null> {\\n    const filePath = this.getTokenFilePath(email);\\n    if (!(await fs.pathExists(filePath))) return null;\\n\\n    try {\\n      const encrypted: EncryptedData = await fs.readJSON(filePath);\\n      const key = await this.keyStore.getKey();\\n      return this.decrypt(encrypted, key);\\n    } catch (error) {\\n      console.error(`[SecureStorage] Failed to load/decrypt token for ${email}:`, error);\\n      return null;\\n    }\\n  }\\n\\n  async deleteToken(email: string): Promise<void> {\\n    const filePath = this.getTokenFilePath(email);\\n    await fs.remove(filePath);\\n  }\\n\\n  async listAccounts(): Promise<string[]> {\\n    const files = await fs.readdir(this.tokenDir);\\n    return files\\n      .filter(f => f.endsWith('.enc'))\\n      .map(f => f.replace('.enc', '').replace(/_/g, '.'));\\n  }\\n\\n  private getTokenFilePath(email: string): string {\\n    const safeEmail = email.replace(/[^a-zA-Z0-9]/g, '_');\\n    return path.join(this.tokenDir, `${safeEmail}.enc`);\\n  }\\n\\n  private encrypt(data: any, key: Buffer): EncryptedData {\\n    const iv = crypto.randomBytes(12);\\n    const cipher = crypto.createCipheriv('aes-256-gcm', key, iv);\\n    \\n    const plaintext = JSON.stringify(data);\\n    let encrypted = cipher.update(plaintext, 'utf8', 'hex');\\n    encrypted += cipher.final('hex');\\n\\n    return {\\n      iv: iv.toString('hex'),\\n      authTag: cipher.getAuthTag().toString('hex'),\\n      data: encrypted,\\n      algorithm: 'aes-256-gcm',\\n      version: 1\\n    };\\n  }\\n\\n  private decrypt(encrypted: EncryptedData, key: Buffer): any {\\n    if (encrypted.algorithm !== 'aes-256-gcm') {\\n      throw new Error(`Unsupported algorithm: ${encrypted.algorithm}`);\\n    }\\n\\n    const decipher = crypto.createDecipheriv(\\n      'aes-256-gcm',\\n      key,\\n      Buffer.from(encrypted.iv, 'hex')\\n    );\\n    \\n    decipher.setAuthTag(Buffer.from(encrypted.authTag, 'hex'));\\n\\n    let decrypted = decipher.update(encrypted.data, 'hex', 'utf8');\\n    decrypted += decipher.final('utf8');\\n\\n    return JSON.parse(decrypted);\\n  }\\n}\\n\"\n    }\n  ]\n}\n```",
